Legal teams need to track specific clauses across multiple contracts. Your task is to build a 
small web application that helps users to track and maintain which contracts contain which 
types of clauses. For simplicity, we assume a legal clause is always represented by a single 
sentence. 
Core Requirements 
Build an application where users can: 
1. Upload contracts - plain text or markdown files  
2. View document and label clause types (e.g., "Limitation of Liability", "Termination for 
Convenience", "Non-Compete") - user should be able to label single sentences with 
clause type 
3. View a dashboard with document list - with options for search, filter and grouping 
Technical Requirements 
● Backend: Python (Flask or FastAPI preferred) 
● Frontend: Angular 
● Database: SQLite 
● Containerization: Provide a Dockerfile and docker-compose.yml so we can run it 
with docker-compose up 
What We're Looking For 
● Clean, maintainable code structure 
● A working API with reasonable endpoint design 
● An intuitive UI which supports the user with labeling clause types 
● Database schema that fits the domain 
Bonus Points (optional) 
● Tests for critical paths 
● Brief notes on how you'd extend this (scaling, AI features, etc.) 
Deliverables 
● GitHub repository (public or invite us) 
● README explaining setup and your design decisions 
Time Expectation 
3–4 hours maximum. We're looking for a UX which is intuitive, self-explaining and appealing. 
We want to see how you think, structure code, and make decisions. The backend code should 
be minimal.  
We'll extend this together in a pair programming session (by adding an automatic labeling step)